      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@tanorix: But the point of this question is about <i>iterating</i> over the returned value. That doesn&#39;t modify it. That&#39;s why the return type of <code>emptyIfNull</code> is <code>Iterable&lt;T&gt;</code> - there&#39;s the unfortunate <code>remove</code> method on <code>Iterator&lt;T&gt;</code>, but that&#39;s the only mutable aspect of it (and if you&#39;ve got an empty collection, why are you trying to remove anything from it?) It&#39;s not clear what you&#39;re objecting to here."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 11683,
      "reputation" : 1520502,
      "user_id" : 22656,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 86,
