    },
    "is_accepted" : true,
    "score" : 257,
    "last_activity_date" : 1265961297,
    "last_edit_date" : 1265961297,
    "creation_date" : 1265956250,
    "answer_id" : 2250056,
    "question_id" : 2250031,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>You should better verify where you get that list from. </p>\n\n<p>An empty list is all you need, because an empty list won't fail.</p>\n\n<p>If you get this list from somewhere else and don't know if it is ok or not you could create a utility method and use it like this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>for( Object o : safe( list ) ) {\n   // do whatever \n }\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>And of course <code>safe</code> would be:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public static List safe( List other ) {\n    return other == null ? Collections.EMPTY_LIST : other;\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 93884,
      "reputation" : 12277,
      "user_id" : 256660,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 75,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/41a2f4e69020199eb64181983156c2bf?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Lombo",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/256660/lombo"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 9,
    "last_activity_date" : 1265956475,
    "creation_date" : 1265956475,
    "answer_id" : 2250066,
    "question_id" : 2250031,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>If you are getting that <code>List</code> from a method call that you implement, then don't return <code>null</code>, return an empty <code>List</code>.</p>\n\n<p>If you can't change the implementation then you are stuck with the <code>null</code> check. If it should't be <code>null</code>, then throw an exception.</p>\n\n<p>I would not go for the helper method that returns an empty list because it may be useful some times but then you would get used to call it in every loop you make possibly hiding some bugs.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 192641,
      "reputation" : 334,
      "user_id" : 433900,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/17b88a67f6e771cf9b41fcfffdc917e0?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Nico de Wet",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/433900/nico-de-wet"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1377742293,
    "creation_date" : 1377742293,
    "answer_id" : 18501248,
    "question_id" : 2250031,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Another way to effectively guard against a null in a for loop is to wrap your collection with Google Guava's <a href=\"http://docs.guava-libraries.googlecode.com/git/javadoc/com/google/common/base/Optional.html\" rel=\"nofollow\"><code>Optional&lt;T&gt;</code></a> as this, one hopes, makes the possibility of an effectively empty collection clear since the client would be expected to check if the collection is present with <code>Optional.isPresent()</code>.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1749035,
      "reputation" : 534,
      "user_id" : 1598572,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 53,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/75bcbbb580925c3e959dd60eea2053e1?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Haris Iltifat",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1598572/haris-iltifat"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1721825116,
    "last_edit_date" : 1721825116,
    "creation_date" : 1439478690,
    "answer_id" : 31992161,
    "question_id" : 2250031,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I have modified another answer so you don't need to cast as an Object:</p>\n<pre><code>public static &lt;T&gt; List&lt;T&gt; safeClient( List&lt;T&gt; other ) {\n            return other == null ? Collections.EMPTY_LIST : other;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Then simply call the List with:</p>\n<pre><code>for (MyOwnObject ownObject : safeClient(someList)) {\n    // do whatever\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Explanation:\nMyOwnObject: If <code>List&lt;Integer&gt;</code> then MyOwnObject will be an Integer in this case.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 8414515,
      "reputation" : 1,
      "user_id" : 6315386,
      "user_type" : "unregistered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f0768d5fd36e40510f1e1b2420be5f7e?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "user6315386",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6315386/user6315386"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : -5,
    "last_activity_date" : 1463423170,
    "last_edit_date" : 1463423170,
    "creation_date" : 1462885595,
    "answer_id" : 37139467,
    "question_id" : 2250031,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<pre><code>for (Object object : someList) {\n\n   // do whatever\n}  throws the null pointer exception.\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1600677,
      "reputation" : 3111,
      "user_id" : 1481755,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 69,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/QKO7e.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "sdc",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1481755/sdc"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 13,
    "last_activity_date" : 1546944620,
    "last_edit_date" : 1546944620,
    "creation_date" : 1472065202,
    "answer_id" : 39131123,
    "question_id" : 2250031,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Use <code>ArrayUtils.nullToEmpty</code> from the <code>commons-lang</code> library for Arrays</p>\n\n<pre><code>for( Object o : ArrayUtils.nullToEmpty(list) ) {\n   // do whatever \n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This functionality exists in the <code>commons-lang</code> library, which is included in most Java projects.</p>\n\n<pre><code>// ArrayUtils.nullToEmpty source code \npublic static Object[] nullToEmpty(final Object[] array) {\n    if (isEmpty(array)) {\n        return EMPTY_OBJECT_ARRAY;\n    }\n    return array;\n}\n\n// ArrayUtils.isEmpty source code\npublic static boolean isEmpty(final Object[] array) {\n    return array == null || array.length == 0;\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This is the same as the answer given by @OscarRyz, but for the sake of the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Don%27t_repeat_yourself\" rel=\"noreferrer\">DRY</a> mantra, I believe it is worth noting. See the <a href=\"https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-lang/\" rel=\"noreferrer\">commons-lang</a> project page. Here is the <code>nullToEmpty</code> API <a href=\"https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-lang/javadocs/api-3.4/org/apache/commons/lang3/ArrayUtils.html#nullToEmpty(java.lang.Object[])\" rel=\"noreferrer\">documentation</a> and <a href=\"https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-lang/javadocs/api-3.4/src-html/org/apache/commons/lang3/ArrayUtils.html#line.474\" rel=\"noreferrer\">source</a></p>\n\n<p>Maven entry to include <code>commons-lang</code> in your project if it is not already. </p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;dependency&gt;\n    &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.commons&lt;/groupId&gt;\n    &lt;artifactId&gt;commons-lang3&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n    &lt;version&gt;3.4&lt;/version&gt;\n&lt;/dependency&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Unfortunately, <code>commons-lang</code> doesn't provide this functionality for <code>List</code> types. In this case you would have to use a helper method as previously mentioned.</p>\n\n<pre><code>public static &lt;E&gt; List&lt;E&gt; nullToEmpty(List&lt;E&gt; list)\n{\n    if(list == null || list.isEmpty())\n    {\n        return Collections.emptyList();\n    }\n    return list;\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
