    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1473875834,
    "creation_date" : 1473875834,
    "answer_id" : 39496827,
    "question_id" : 2250031,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>For anyone uninterested in writing their own static null safety method you can use: commons-lang's <code>org.apache.commons.lang.ObjectUtils.defaultIfNull(Object, Object)</code>. For example: </p>\n\n<pre><code>    for (final String item : \n    (List&lt;String&gt;)ObjectUtils.defaultIfNull(items, Collections.emptyList())) { ... }\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-lang/apidocs/org/apache/commons/lang3/ObjectUtils.html#defaultIfNull(T,%20T)\" rel=\"nofollow\">ObjectUtils.defaultIfNull JavaDoc</a></p>\n"
  }, {
