    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1509718137,
    "creation_date" : 1509718137,
    "answer_id" : 47097764,
    "question_id" : 2250031,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Use, <code>CollectionUtils.isEmpty(Collection coll)</code> method which is Null-safe check if the specified collection is empty. </p>\n\n<p>for this <code>import org.apache.commons.collections.CollectionUtils</code>.</p>\n\n<p>Maven dependency</p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;dependency&gt;\n    &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.commons&lt;/groupId&gt;\n    &lt;artifactId&gt;commons-collections4&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n    &lt;version&gt;4.0&lt;/version&gt;\n&lt;/dependency&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7388280,
      "reputation" : 446,
      "user_id" : 5622596,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/06aac7d37adf26938875fd4139b7d5ff?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "jspek",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5622596/jspek"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1734567265,
    "last_edit_date" : 1734567265,
    "creation_date" : 1734565920,
    "answer_id" : 79292801,
    "question_id" : 2250031,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Using only Java here is an idea:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-none prettyprint-override\"><code>List&lt;SomeType&gt; someList= Objects.requireNonNullElse(listSource, new ArrayList&lt;&gt;());\nfor(var someElement: someList)){\n  //...           \n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>There are all sorts of variations to this approach.\nFor example do you need someList to be immutable if empty? Then instead of an <code>new ArrayList&lt;&gt;()</code> you can use <code>List.of()</code>.\nThis is just an example, feel free to use whichever data structure is best.</p>\n"
  } ],
