  "question_id" : 2250031,
  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2250031/null-check-in-an-enhanced-for-loop",
  "title" : "Null check in an enhanced for loop",
  "body" : "<p>What is the best way to guard against null in a for loop in Java? </p>\n\n<p>This seems ugly :</p>\n\n<pre><code>if (someList != null) {\n    for (Object object : someList) {\n        // do whatever\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Or</p>\n\n<pre><code>if (someList == null) {\n    return; // Or throw ex\n}\nfor (Object object : someList) {\n    // do whatever\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>There might not be any other way. Should they have put it in the <code>for</code> construct itself, if it is null then don't run the loop?</p>\n"
}